verses.verse: (For the choir director. A Song. A Psalm.) <S%H7321>Shout<s%> <S%H7321>joyfully<s%> to <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H776>earth;<s%>
<S%H2167>Sing<s%> the <S%H9202>glory<s%> of His <S%H8034>name;<s%> <S%H7760>Make<s%> His <S%H8416>praise<s%> <S%H9202>glorious.<s%>

<S%H559>Say<s%> to <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H4100>"How<s%> <S%H3372>awesome<s%> are Thy <S%H4639>works!<s%> Because of the <S%H7230>greatness<s%> of Thy <S%H5797>power<s%> Thine <S%H340>enemies<s%> will <S%H3584>give<s%> <S%H3584>feigned<s%> <S%H3584>obedience<s%> to Thee.

<S%H3605>"All<s%> the <S%H776>earth<s%> will <S%H7812>worship<s%> Thee, And will <S%H2167>sing<s%> <S%H2167>praises<s%> to Thee; They will <S%H2167>sing<s%> <S%H2167>praises<s%> to Thy <S%H8034>name.<s%>" <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>

<S%H1980>Come<s%> and <S%H7200>see<s%> the <S%H9282>works<s%> of <S%H430>God,<s%> [Who is] <S%H3372>awesome<s%> in [His] <S%H5949>deeds<s%> <S%H5921>toward<s%> the <S%H1121>sons<s%> of <S%H120>men.<s%>

He <S%H2015>turned<s%> the <S%H3220>sea<s%> into <S%H3004>dry<s%> <S%H3004>land;<s%> They <S%H5674>passed<s%> through the <S%H5104>river<s%> on <S%H7272>foot;<s%> <S%H8033>There<s%> let us <S%H8055>rejoice<s%> in Him!

He <S%H4910>rules<s%> by His <S%H1369>might<s%> <S%H5703>forever;<s%> His <S%H5869>eyes<s%> <S%H6822>keep<s%> <S%H6822>watch<s%> on the <S%H1471>nations;<s%> Let not the <S%H5637>rebellious<s%> <S%H7311>exalt<s%> themselves. <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
<S%H1288>Bless<s%> our <S%H430>God,<s%> O <S%H5971>peoples,<s%> And <S%H8085>sound<s%> <S%H6963><s%> His <S%H8416>praise<s%> abroad,
Who <S%H7760>keeps<s%> us in <S%H9132>life,<s%> And does not <S%H5414>allow<s%> our <S%H7272>feet<s%> to <S%H4131>slip.<s%>
For Thou hast <S%H974>tried<s%> us, O <S%H430>God;<s%> Thou hast <S%H6884>refined<s%> us as <S%H3701>silver<s%> is <S%H6884>refined.<s%>
Thou didst <S%H935>bring<s%> us into the <S%H9287>net;<s%> Thou didst <S%H7760>lay<s%> an <S%H4157>oppressive<s%> <S%H4157>burden<s%> upon our <S%H4975>loins.<s%>

Thou didst make <S%H582>men<s%> <S%H7392>ride<s%> over our <S%H7218>heads;<s%> We <S%H935>went<s%> through <S%H784>fire<s%> and through <S%H4325>water;<s%> Yet Thou didst <S%H3318>bring<s%> us out into [a place of] <S%H7310>abundance.<s%>
I shall <S%H935>come<s%> into Thy <S%H1004>house<s%> with <S%H5930>burnt<s%> <S%H5930>offerings;<s%> I shall <S%H9608>pay<s%> Thee my <S%H5088>vows,<s%>
<S%H834>Which<s%> my <S%H8193>lips<s%> <S%H6475>uttered<s%> And my <S%H6310>mouth<s%> <S%H1696>spoke<s%> when I was in <S%H9496>distress.<s%>

I shall <S%H5927>offer<s%> to Thee <S%H5930>burnt<s%> <S%H5930>offerings<s%> of <S%H4220>fat<s%> <S%H4220>beasts,<s%> With the <S%H7004>smoke<s%> of <S%H352>rams;<s%> I shall <S%H6213>make<s%> [an offering of] <S%H1241>bulls<s%> with <S%H6260>male<s%> <S%H6260>goats.<s%> <S%H5542>Selah.<s%>
<S%H1980>Come<s%> [and] <S%H8085>hear,<s%> <S%H3605>all<s%> who <S%H3372>fear<s%> <S%H430>God,<s%> And I will <S%H5608>tell<s%> of <S%H834>what<s%> He has <S%H6213>done<s%> for my <S%H5315>soul.<s%>
I <S%H7121>cried<s%> to Him with my <S%H6310>mouth,<s%> And He was <S%H7311>extolled<s%> with my <S%H3956>tongue.<s%>
<S%H518>If<s%> I <S%H7200>regard<s%> <S%H205>wickedness<s%> in my <S%H3820>heart,<s%> The <S%H136>Lord<s%> will not <S%H8085>hear;<s%>
But <S%H403>certainly<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> has <S%H8085>heard;<s%> He has <S%H7181>given<s%> <S%H7181>heed<s%> to the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of my <S%H8605>prayer.<s%>
<S%H1288>Blessed<s%> be <S%H430>God,<s%> <S%H834>Who<s%> has not <S%H5493>turned<s%> <S%H5493>away<s%> my <S%H8605>prayer,<s%> <S%H3808>Nor<s%> His <S%H2617>lovingkindness<s%> from me.
